@startuml epicd-workitem-state
' epicd — State diagram: a Task's lifecycle across the authoring & execution pipelines.
' User-visible behaviour: what states a user watches a Task move through in the multi-lane list.
' lane = pipeline_id ; role (Basic/primitive vs Epic/compound) = orthogonal type axis ;
' status shown as "Role: State" (config) — bare state = engine pipeline state.

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam state {
  BorderColor #555555
  BackgroundColor #E8F0FE
  BackgroundColor<<gate>> #FFE0B2
  BackgroundColor<<human>> #C8E6C9
  BackgroundColor<<terminal>> #E0E0E0
}

title epicd — Work-item lifecycle (State diagram; lane = pipeline_id, role orthogonal)

[*] --> Draft : Human captures\n(kind:feature/chore/epic)

state "Authoring lane  (pipeline_id = authoring)" as Authoring {
  state Draft
  state Refining
  state Backlog <<gate>>
  Draft --> Refining : scanner claims\n(basic-draft / epic-draft)
  Refining --> Backlog : refine done\n(feature→Proposal+Plan /\nchore→checklist / epic→plan)
  note right of Refining
    Routed by **kind** label:
    feature-to-backlog / task-to-backlog / epic-to-backlog.
    DRAFT is a STATE here (loop-draft), not a drafts/ folder.
  end note
}

Backlog --> Ready : **Human promote gate**\n(authoring → execution)

state "Execution lane  (pipeline_id = execution)" as Execution {
  state Ready
  state "In Progress" as InProgress
  state Decomposing
  state "Awaiting Children" as Awaiting
  state Evaluating

  state chooseRole <<choice>>
  Ready --> chooseRole : scanner\n(basic-ready / epic-ready)
  chooseRole --> InProgress : role = primitive (Basic)\nfeature→implement / chore→checklist
  chooseRole --> Decomposing : role = compound (Epic)

  Decomposing --> Awaiting : creates children\n(role stays compound)
  Awaiting --> Evaluating : all children terminal\n(epic-eval-due)

  note bottom of InProgress
    engine.complete() → merge/advance →
    **adjudicate DoD (ENG-8)**: engine re-runs DoD,
    worker may NOT self-write `done`.
  end note
}

state "Done" as Done <<terminal>>
state "Needs Human" as NeedsHuman <<human>>

InProgress --> Done : DoD pass
InProgress --> NeedsHuman : DoD fail / conflict
Evaluating --> Done : epic satisfied
Evaluating --> NeedsHuman : epic escalate

NeedsHuman --> Ready : Human gate-review\n(approve / re-open)
NeedsHuman --> [*] : Human gate-review (reject / archive)
Done --> [*]

note as N_role
  **role** is DERIVED from tree position (ADR-011 D-1.1):
  leaf ⇒ primitive (Basic) · has children ⇒ compound (Epic).
  Decomposing FLIPS a task primitive→compound.
  role is the TYPE axis — orthogonal to lane(=pipeline_id).
end note
note as N_stale
  **stale-in-progress**: In Progress > 30 min without update →
  informational flag only; no auto state change; human decides.
end note

@enduml
